Length: 1.65-2.05 mm (avg. 1.89 mm); width: 1.50-1.77 mm (avg. 1.62 mm). This species is extremely similar to the preceding (

P. serratus

), but differs consistently in being broader in body form (Fig. 
7E
), having the median portion of the frontal stria detached from the lateral portions rather than continuous across the frons, the pronotal disk more strongly depressed along the lateral margin, and in having sparser dorsal ground punctation, along with slightly lower density of secondary lateral pronotal punctures. The male genitalia exhibit no obvious differences from that of the 

P. serratus

(Fig. 
8C, D
).
